  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-502">
    <command xml:space="preserve">open purple</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You open the purple capsa of opening, revealing a scroll of rezrov.&#x000A;&#x000A;As you open the purple capsa, an almost-palpable wave of force emanates from it, as the power of the revealed scroll of rezrov is released.&#x000A;&#x000A;The huge double doors to the Great Hall clicks as it unlocks!&#x000A;The magic of the gold capsa of Down prevents it from being opened.&#x000A;The huge double doors to the Great Hall flies open!&#x000A;The straps and buckles on your rucksack fly open and it falls!&#x000A;&#x000A;Dropped.&#x000A;&#x000A;From... well, from everywhere in the Aerie, it seems, Woodpeckers start drumming out messages in their Pounding dialect:  "Intruder! Estimated direction is..." and then each one individually seems to be telegraphing the direction from them to you.  You can't discern any one drummer from any other drummer, but you can at least tell that each seems to be drumming on sheets of metal that differ from each other, as the frequencies are all different from each other.  That makes the information somewhat useless to you, because you've not been trained to distinguish Pounding at different frequencies.  And because you already know where you are.  Sadly, the Raven Guards are indeed trained to distinguish Pounding frequencies, and they don't know where you are.&#x000A;&#x000A;Or they didn't, at least.&#x000A;&#x000A;closeness: 1.&#x000A;&#x000A;The momentum you had from your dive wears off.  &#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-503"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-503">
    <command xml:space="preserve">u</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north, well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  In the center of the Aerie (and directly below you) is the Great Hall.  Other royal aeries dot the forest in the distance, but this complex holds your quarry.&#x000A;&#x000A;closeness: 2.&#x000A;You've barely left Great Hall Landing Cradle when a squad of Raven Guards wheels in from behind, hot on your tail!&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-504"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-504">
    <command xml:space="preserve">z</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Time passes.&#x000A;&#x000A;closeness: 3.&#x000A;The guards charge, but you manage to evade their uncoordinated attack.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-505"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-505">
    <command xml:space="preserve">z</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Time passes.&#x000A;&#x000A;closeness: 4.&#x000A;Two guards snap at you, and while both touch nothing but feathers, a third slashes you with his silvered talons.  They're about to overwhelm you.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-506"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-506">
    <command xml:space="preserve">scenes</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Scene 'Entire Game' playing (for 15 mins now)&#x000A;Scene 'Starting Off' ended&#x000A;Scene 'Everything Is Open' playing (for 4 mins now)&#x000A;Scene 'Go go go' playing (for 14 mins now)&#x000A;Scene 'Momentum' ended&#x000A;Scene 'Super-momentum' ended&#x000A;Scene 'Being Chased' playing (for 4 mins now)&#x000A;Scene 'Not Recovering' playing (for 0 mins now)&#x000A;(Scene monitoring now switched on. Type "scenes off" to switch it off again.)&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-507"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-507">
    <command xml:space="preserve">showme woodpeckers</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Woodpeckers - person&#x000A;location: in the Void&#x000A;unlit, inedible, portable; transparent, male; singular-named, proper-named; activated&#x000A;description: "I dunno if you'll ever actually see these guys; they just sound the alarms from offstage."&#x000A;initial appearance: none&#x000A;carrying capacity: 100&#x000A;printed name: "Woodpeckers"&#x000A;printed plural name: "people"&#x000A;indefinite article: none&#x000A;list grouping key: none&#x000A;reset state: 0&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-508"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-508">
    <command xml:space="preserve">d</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You dive blindingly fast towards the Aerie through the fog, and the mist swallows you with nary an eddy.&#x000A;&#x000A;Great Hall Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Great Hall spreads out over nearly a quarter of the vast building.  During your time here, you learned this was so that when a number of important guests and their retinues arrive at the same time, they can land simultaneously, instead of one after the other, which some would invariably take as meaning "in order of importance".  The huge double doors to the Great Hall are on the west side of the landing cradle, and unguarded.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the north is the Royal Quarters and Gardens, the Librum to the east, and as always, you can return to the skies or descend to the forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see a leather rucksack (in which are a purple capsa of opening (in which is a scroll of rezrov), a gold capsa of Down (closed), and a red capsa of hasten (in which is a scroll of quiste)) here.&#x000A;&#x000A;[Scene 'Super-momentum' begins]&#x000A;closeness: 5.&#x000A;You expertly twist at breakneck speeds, weaving through three Ash trunks, over a branch, and around and behind a Redwood, where you halt, twist, and dive straight down the trunk, out of view of any stray Raven.&#x000A;&#x000A;The Raven's frustrated caws echo in the mist, and you plot a now-unseen course returning to the familiar currents above the Aerie.  In time, the woodpeckers cease their drumming, and the cawing fades as well.  Protocol would dictate that they return to guarding priority items, but increase patrols.&#x000A;&#x000A;High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north, well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  In the center of the Aerie (and directly below you) is the Great Hall.  Other royal aeries dot the forest in the distance, but this complex holds your quarry.&#x000A;&#x000A;[Scene 'Being Chased' ends]&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-461">
    <command xml:space="preserve">summon mist</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You draw even more moisture into the air, and feed it into the mist.  As it thickens, you feel safer, as you always do in the midst of clouds.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
