  <item nodeId="node-481">
    <command xml:space="preserve">u</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north, well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  In the center of the Aerie (and directly below you) is the Great Hall.  Other royal aeries dot the forest in the distance, but this complex holds your quarry.&#x000A;&#x000A;Your summoned mist thins back to equilibrium.  Still thick enough to mostly obscure you, but you'll have to be careful.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-482"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-482">
    <command xml:space="preserve">d</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You tuck in your wings and dive down towards the Aerie, thrilling to the misty wind streaming through your feathers.&#x000A;&#x000A;Great Hall Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Great Hall spreads out over nearly a quarter of the vast building.  During your time here, you learned this was so that when a number of important guests and their retinues arrive at the same time, they can land simultaneously, instead of one after the other, which some would invariably take as meaning "in order of importance".  The huge double doors to the Great Hall are on the west side of the landing cradle, and unguarded.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the north is the Royal Quarters and Gardens, the Librum to the east, and as always, you can return to the skies or descend to the forest.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see a leather rucksack (in which are a purple capsa of opening (in which is a scroll of rezrov), a gold capsa of Down (closed), and a red capsa of hasten (closed)) here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-483"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-483">
    <command xml:space="preserve">get rucksack</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Taken.&#x000A;&#x000A;The momentum you had from your dive wears off.  Fun while it lasted!&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-484"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-484">
    <command xml:space="preserve">e</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Librum Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Librum is beautifully set with interlocking redwood and pine, suggesting shelves of books.  The Librum Door leads inward to the Librum itself.&#x000A;&#x000A;To the west is the Great Hall, and to the northwest is the Royal Quarters and Gardens.  You can also re-ascend to the skies or descend to the forest below.&#x000A;&#x000A;A lone Raven guard stands in front of the door, dark eyes shifting as she watches the mist.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-485"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-485">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x door</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">A canted open hatch to the Librum, on the east side of the landing cradle.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-486"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-486">
    <command xml:space="preserve">close purple</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You close the purple capsa of opening.&#x000A;&#x000A;The guard closes the Librum door.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-487"/>
    </children>
  </item>
